FBIS4-54406 "dreeu083__a94020" FBIS-EEU-94-083-A Daily Report 28 Apr 1994 ANNEX Czech Republic Bulgaria's Daskalov Arrives, Meets Officials Bulgaria's Daskalov Arrives, Meets Officials Daskalov Backs `Tough Approach' for Peace AU2904091894 Prague CTK in English 1930 GMT 28 Apr 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU2904091894 Prague CTK English BFN [Text] Prague, April 28 (CTK) -- Bulgarian-Czech relations were appreciated as good by Czech Parliament Chairman Milan Uhde and visiting Bulgarian Foreign Minister Stanislav Daskalov at their meeting today. Uhde and Daskalov welcomed the signing of an agreement on cooperation between the two countries' foreign ministries and the fact that agreements on the prevention of double taxation and on investment protection were under preparation, Uhde told CTK after the meeting. Regarding the conflict in the former Yugoslavia Daskalov voiced the view that tough approach towards all who violate peace in the region should be adopted and that the United States, Russia, and NATO should equally participate in solving the situation. Daskalov also met Czech Premier Vaclav Klaus today.
